      • canTileBeMovedOn

        public boolean canTileBeMovedOn​(int row,
                                int column)
        Gets whether tile on specified position may be moved on. All tiles that are empty or contain a transparent entity may be moved on.
        Parameters:
        row - row in boardArray.
        column - column in boardArray.
        Returns:
        returns true if tile can be moved on and false if it can not be moved on or is out of bounds.

      • isTileEmpty

        public boolean isTileEmpty​(int row,
                           int column)
        Gets whether tile on specified position is empty. Tiles out of bounds are considered empty.
        Parameters:
        row - row in boardArray.
        column - column in boardArray.
        Returns:
        returns true if tile can be moved on and false if it can not be moved on or is out of bounds.

      • getExplosionAtPos

        public ExplosionTile getExplosionAtPos​(int rowPos,
                                       int colPos)
        Gets ExplosionTile on specified position. Explosion does NOT count as tile content.
        Parameters:
        rowPos - row in boardArray.
        colPos - column in boardArray.
        Returns:
        returns null if requested pos does is not exploding or if it is out od bounds.

      • setExplosionAtPos

        public void setExplosionAtPos​(int rowPos,
                              int colPos,
                              ExplosionTile e)
        Sets ExplosionTile on specified position. Explosion does NOT count as tile content. If requested position is out of bounds the incident is logged but no error occurs.
        Parameters:
        rowPos - row in boardArray.
        colPos - column in boardArray.

      • removeExplosion

        public void removeExplosion​(int rowPos,
                            int colPos)
        Removes ExplosionTile on specified position. Explosion does NOT count as tile content. If requested position is out of bounds the incident is logged but no error occurs. If called on a non-exploding tile nothing happens.
        Parameters:
        rowPos - row in boardArray.
        colPos - column in boardArray.

      • isTilePosExploding

        public boolean isTilePosExploding​(int rowPos,
                                  int colPos)
        Gets whether tile on specified position is exploding. If requested position is out of bounds the incident is logged but no error occurs.
        Parameters:
        rowPos - row in boardArray.
        colPos - column in boardArray.
        Returns:
        returns false if requested position is out od bound or if it contains no explosion. Else returns true.
